# .trivyignore — Accepted Trivy vulnerability exceptions
#
# FORMAT: CVE-ID  # justification | review-by: YYYY-MM-DD
#
# Rules (per JD-69 / docs/SECURITY.md):
#   1. Every entry MUST include: CVE ID, justification, and a review-by date.
#   2. Entries are reviewed quarterly — stale ignores fail the CI audit job.
#   3. Blanket OS-package exclusions are NOT permitted.
#   4. Use `--ignore-unfixed` in CI so only known-fixed vulns must be accepted here.
#
# Example (uncomment and adjust when a real CVE needs an exception):
# CVE-2024-00000  # Not exploitable in our runtime — no user input reaches this codepath | review-by: 2026-09-01
